There is excitement among the broad spectrum of the membership of the Musical Copyright Society Nigeria Ltd/Gte as it prepares for its Annual General Meeting (AGM) for the year 2022. According to a statement from MCSN, the AGM is scheduled to hold on June 29, 2022, and one of the businesses fixed for the day is the elections into the Board (General Council) of the Society. The statement further noted that the AGM will also see to the receipt and consideration of the Chairman’s report of events and developments as of December 2021 as well as the Directors’ Report for the year ended December 2021, the Financial Reports for the year ended December 2021 and the Auditors’ Reports thereon.   Structured music industry will impact Nigeria’s economy,…     Nuno Zigi set for debut EP NDO     Obi Asika speaks on Journey of the Beats documentary   Commenting on the preparation of MCSN for the AGM, the Chief Executive Officer of the Society, Mayo Ayilaran assured us that everything has been put in place to make the AGM successful. Reacting to a question, Ayilaran explained that the elections into the General Council (Board) of the Society have become necessary because of the need to make the board more representative of the various genre of music in the country.